blog.title: The Beta Pokedex project
blog.description:
A blog dedicated to my art project of drawing official-looking illustrations for
all beta version Pokemon that were found from the Pokemon Gold Demo at Spaceworld 1997.

Reposting is ok! Just do NOT remove my signature or url from the images. If you want to use my artwork without the signature (for Youtube thumbnails for example), a link to this blog must be provided.

You can find me and my other work in: skudde.deviantart.com / skudde.tumblr.com / @skuddeouo on Twitter

(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Basculin
body:
550: Basculin

You’d swear this would be Gen 5’s Magikarp, an unassuming fish that evolves into a frigging sea serpent right? Wrong. It’s just… Basculin. Unova needed some fish. Here’s some fish. No, wait, here’s two fish in one Pokemon! Basculin comes in two color varieties that are just cosmetic differences. And the two hate each other with a burning passion. Which makes me think of Beta Fish a bit. But eh.

Personal Score: 6/10

Those sure are some fish. Some aight looking fish, but just fish.

[Archive]

summary: Fakemon doodles! First up is the Bug/Water Diving Beetle named Scubeetle! Ability is Swift Swim - Next we have a Water/Steel...
caption: Fakemon doodles! First up is the Bug/Water Diving Beetle named Scubeetle! Ability is Swift Swim - Next we have a Water/Steel SAWfish hehe, Ability is Intimidate!  Ok third one is a bit silly- I wanted to design a Poke for a hypothetical Canada themed Region, and came up with these sports/hockey birds, based after three Canadaland birbs; the Chickadee, Cardinal, and Blue Jay!
